task.summary: Default task
A first commit to a great project.
completed a first draft of how to populate the config object.
The main entry point has been thoroughly hacked into more managable pieces to allow for an easier overview of the project.
Config now parses one or two config JSON files depending on user input, and keeps the config in the config object for easy access.
Abstracts away the internals of the connections to the wanted DB, only supporting mongoDB at the moment.
A sample config file on the important parts for the app.
Init now handles everything from setting up the app with sane settings and proper routing, to starting the app and finally handle terminations gracefully.
Abstracts away the internals of setting up a logger and exposes a uniform interface to log. Supports winston and console logging.
Added hiredis for future experimentation with storing sessions using redis.
Shuffled files around for better overview.
Foundation for a fully functional crud app is laid.
Cleared up and extended the routing setup.
Secured the app from csrf and some minor cleanups.
Login prework.
Minor adjustments to... Everything.
Renamed to reflect the action taken
Renamed to include the full MVC per page in each directory.
Added a few options, removed option to freely choose db adapter.
A few simple first jade templates.
Hammered out each model's responsibilities very roughly as well as an added queries interface to use for all models.
Changed workflow and duty for each script/function.
Added more to do for the controllers.
register, login, logout fully functional
Wow much changes so half-decent

A fully functional skeleton.
0.1.0
Minor adjustments and tweaks.
Anything goes!
